i'm the mother of 4 "children" - ages 23-28.  i worked outside the home as they were growing up and i know how important it is to want to do the best for our children and to make the world a better place for them. 
my favorite quote is attributed to ralph waldo emerson and there is also a line of thinking that says it couldn't be emerson.  really, does it matter?  it's the message that matters  - here's an abbreviated version - 

The definition of success:
To laugh often and much; 
To win the . . .  affection of children;
To earn the appreciation of honest critics and endure the betrayal of false friends;
To appreciate beauty, 
To find the best in others;
To leave the world a bit better, whether by a garden patch or a redeemed social condition;
To know even one life has breathed easier because you have lived.
This is to have succeeded."

Thanks to KIVA for giving us an opportunity to help beyond our borders.
